<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1310,1733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,201,1311,1337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Notes</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis box="[209,234,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">—</emphasis>
In the protologue of 
<emphasis box="[487,723,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<taxonomicName box="[487,719,1310,1336]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">Lobelia glazioviana</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zahlbruckner, A." box="[735,973,1310,1337]" firstAuthor="Zahlbruckner" journalOrPublisher="Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra den Naturhistoriske Forening i Kjobenhavn" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="67 - 71" part="38" refId="ref8589" refString="Zahlbruckner, A. (1896) Lobeliaceae brasiliensis e collectionibus imprimes Dr. A. Glaziou. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra den Naturhistoriske Forening i Kjobenhavn 38: 67 - 71." title="Lobeliaceae brasiliensis e collectionibus imprimes Dr. A. Glaziou" type="journal article" year="1896">Zahlbruckner (1896)</bibRefCitation>
referred to the specimen 
<emphasis box="[1287,1451,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Glaziou 8148,</emphasis>
collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[278,446,1346,1372]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
and with duplicates in several herbaria. Most duplicates of this collection have “ 
<emphasis box="[1387,1451,1347,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">prope</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[136,303,1382,1408]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
” as their locality, but the specimens [P02870858] and [P02870859] are from “ 
<collectingRegion box="[1193,1313,1382,1408]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
, Campos da Bocaina”. This divergence in locality for the same set of specimens must be due to the fact that they all were collected in the Serra da Bocaina, a region covering both states mentioned in the labels. We indicate the specimen 
<accessionNumber box="[1305,1402,1454,1481]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/W15784" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">W15784</accessionNumber>
as a 
<typeStatus box="[136,239,1490,1516]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">lectotype</typeStatus>
since it was collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[521,686,1490,1516]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
, as described in the protologue, and W was the herbarium where the author carried out most of his research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,1310,1733]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">
<bibRefCitation author="Wimmer, F. E." box="[189,370,1562,1588]" firstAuthor="Wimmer" journalOrPublisher="Repertorium specierum novarum regni vegetabilis" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="241 - 265" part="19" refId="ref8410" refString="Wimmer, F. E. (1924) Lobelioideae. Species et varietates novae ex generibus. Repertorium specierum novarum regni vegetabilis 19: 241 - 265. https: // doi. org / 10.1002 / fedr. 19240191602" title="Lobelioideae. Species et varietates novae ex generibus" type="journal article" year="1924">Wimmer (1924)</bibRefCitation>
dedicated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wimmer" authorityYear="1924" box="[492,741,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zahlbruckneri">
<emphasis box="[492,741,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Lobelia zahlbruckneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to Austrian botanist Zahlbruckner, based only on the specimen 
<emphasis box="[136,287,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">Glaziou 8148</emphasis>
(Hb. Del.). The specimen is housed at G and stamped “Hb. Delessert” on its label. It is thus interpreted as the 
<typeStatus box="[177,275,1634,1660]" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wimmer" authorityYear="1924" box="[311,496,1634,1660]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zahlbruckneri">
<emphasis box="[311,496,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. zahlbruckneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name is unfortunately based on a specimen of the type collection of a previously described species, and thus being taxonomically superfluous. Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wimmer, F. E." box="[894,1074,1670,1697]" editor="Engler, A. &amp; Diels, L." firstAuthor="Wimmer" journalOrPublisher="Akademie- Verlag, Berlin" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" pagination="261 - 813" part="i - viii" refId="ref8487" refString="Wimmer, F. E. (1953) Campanulaceae-Lobelioideae, II. Teil. In: Engler, A. &amp; Diels, L. (Eds.) Das Pflanzenreich IV. 276 b. Akademie- Verlag, Berlin, pp. i - viii, 261 - 813." title="Campanulaceae-Lobelioideae, II. Teil" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Das Pflanzenreich IV. 276 b" year="1953">Wimmer (1953)</bibRefCitation>
noticed his mistake and proposed the synonymization of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wimmer" authorityYear="1924" box="[393,579,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zahlbruckneri">
<emphasis box="[393,579,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. zahlbruckneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Zahlbruckner" authorityYear="1896" box="[656,817,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Campanulaceae" genus="Lobelia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="50" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glazioviana">
<emphasis box="[656,817,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="50">L. glazioviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
